node.text:
Yes, she’s the world’s top-ranked female tennis player, but @NaomiOsaka won us over for her qualities *off* the court. 💖 Soft-spoken yet powerful and always authentic, she brought those same qualities to our new collaboration. The Levi’s® x Naomi Osaka collection, crafted from upcycled denim, takes Levi’s® icons to an unexpected place, celebrating Naomi’s rich heritage with a bold femininity and a sporty attitude—and a bit of her famous dry wit. Plus, you know, crystals and lace-ups. Link in bio.

🎥: @yongwkim 
.

WHERE YOU CAN SHOP THE COLLAB:

Levi’s App (US, UK, France)
Levi.com (Japan)
Levi’s Stores (Harajuku, Osaka, Shanghai, Hong Kong)

This Juneteenth we wrap on our Beauty of Becoming series with the woman who created and directed the short films, Oge Egbuonu. Through telling stories that celebrate the people that society often casts aside, while embracing the unfolding chapters of her own, Oge Egbuonu is becoming. 

Created and Directed by @ogetheyogi
Music by @phantogram

[Video: Oge is sitting in front of a brown background and green leaves with pink and red floral arrangements. She is wearing a black denim shirt with her name embroidered above the front left breast pocket and black denim jeans. Shots of her walking around in a flower labyrinth of various colors and sitting at a wooden desk on a wooden writing on a piece of paper are shown throughout the video.]
